@Reasoning:
LABEL aggregates an arbitrary number of key/value pairs on a single line.
The HIR encoding wraps them in one Array of 2-tuples. Emission iterates
the tuple list, extracting key and value via positional access, and joins
pairs with single spaces. Values containing whitespace are double-quoted
to match dockerfile_printer's quoting heuristic.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Emit "LABEL "; iterate tuples; for each: emit key + "=" + (quoted value
if it contains a space, else raw value); space-separator between pairs;
LF at the end.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_label_call" that takes backend_ptr as Integer, hir_call_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
